{"type":"text","timestamp":1775840284743,"sessionID":"ses_287ac3cbdffe8hzwjoSofINCzZ","part":{"id":"prt_d78544e3c001RhXKagEp8uA3tH","messageID":"msg_d78543cde001r6By756qvmduwz","sessionID":"ses_287ac3cbdffe8hzwjoSofINCzZ","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context to write the proposal. Let me create the proposal.md file for AR-003:","time":{"start":1775840284741,"end":1775840284741}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840319856,"sessionID":"ses_287ac3cbdffe8hzwjoSofINCzZ","part":{"id":"prt_d78545048001ozdT017OMu3JIJ","messageID":"msg_d78543cde001r6By756qvmduwz","sessionID":"ses_287ac3cbdffe8hzwjoSofINCzZ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_3c6fc9aad4f14e86b3d5830c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","content":"# AR-003: CRD Shared Types & Constants\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal defines shared types and constants for the `pkg/apis` module to be used across CRDs in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Centralize common type definitions** - Avoid duplication of types like `ResourceQuota`, `NetworkPolicy`, and lifecycle hooks across multiple CRDs\n2. **Establish naming conventions** - Consistent naming for phases, conditions, and resource types\n3. **Provide reusable validation utilities** - Shared validation functions for common fields\n4. **Enable code generation consistency** - Ensure generated client-go code follows consistent patterns\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - Common type definitions in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n  - Constant definitions for phases and condition types\n  - Shared validation utilities\n  - Documentation of patterns for future CRDs\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - Changes to existing CRD structures (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n  - Client-go code generation changes\n  - Controller logic modifications\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing Shared Types\n\nThe codebase already has several types that could be considered \"shared\":\n\n1. **`ResourceQuota`** (`types.go:80-90`) - CPU, Memory, Storage limits\n2. **`NetworkPolicy`** / `NetworkRule` (`types.go:102-110`) - Network access rules\n3. **`LifecycleHook`** (`types.go:115-123`) - PreStart/PostStop callbacks\n4. **`ContainerSpec`** (`types.go:125-143`) - Container configuration\n5. **`CodeInterpreterSpec`** (`types.go:79-90`) - Embedded interpreter config\n\n### Existing Constants\n\n1. **AgentRuntimePhase** constants (`types.go:26-36`):\n   - `AgentRuntimePhasePending`\n   - `AgentRuntimePhaseRunning`\n   - `AgentRuntimePhaseFailed`\n   - `AgentRuntimePhaseTerminating`\n\n2. **AgentRuntimeConditionType** constants (`types.go:38-48`):\n   - `AgentRuntimeConditionReady`\n   - `AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated`\n   - `AgentRuntimeConditionCodeInterpreterReady`\n\n3. **AgentRuntimeCondition** struct (`types.go:50-64`) - Reusable condition pattern\n\n### Issues Identified\n\n1. **Naming inconsistency**: Types are prefixed with `AgentRuntime` but could be more generic\n2. **No shared validation**: Validation logic in `validation.go:171` for `CodeInterpreter` is specific to that type\n3. **No documentation**: No clear guidelines on which types should be shared vs. CRD-specific\n4. **Tight coupling**: `CodeInterpreterSpec` is embedded in `AgentRuntimeSpec` but may need to be standalone\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. Type Categorization\n\nIntroduce clear categorization for types:\n\n```\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n├── types_common.go      # Shared types (ResourceQuota, NetworkPolicy, etc.)\n├── types_agentruntime.go  # AgentRuntime-specific types\n└── types_codeinterpreter.go # CodeInterpreter-specific types (if needed)\n```\n\n**Rationale:** Improves discoverability and makes it clear which types are intended for reuse.\n\n### 2. Standardize Type Naming\n\nCurrent naming is already consistent with Kubernetes conventions:\n- All types use PascalCase\n- Related types share prefixes (e.g., `AgentRuntimePhase`, `AgentRuntimeCondition`)\n- Embedded structs use descriptive names (`CodeInterpreterSpec`, not just `CodeInterpreter`)\n\n**No changes needed** - current naming follows Kubernetes API conventions.\n\n### 3. Extract Shared Validation\n\nCreate reusable validation functions in `validation.go`:\n\n```go\n// ValidateResourceQuota validates resource quota fields\nfunc ValidateResourceQuota(quota *ResourceQuota, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n\n// ValidateNetworkPolicy validates network policy configuration\nfunc ValidateNetworkPolicy(policy *NetworkPolicy, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n\n// ValidateContainerSpec validates container specification\nfunc ValidateContainerSpec(spec *ContainerSpec, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n```\n\n**Impact:** Reduces code duplication when adding new CRDs that use these types.\n\n### 4. Document Type Usage Patterns\n\nAdd package-level documentation in `doc.go`:\n\n```go\n// Package v1alpha1 defines the AgentCube runtime API types.\n//\n// Shared Types:\n// Types without AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter prefix are intended for reuse:\n// - ResourceQuota: Resource limits and requests\n// - NetworkPolicy/NetworkRule: Network access control\n// - LifecycleHook: Lifecycle callbacks\n// - ContainerSpec: Container configuration\n//\n// CRD-Specific Types:\n// Types prefixed with AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter are specific\n// to those CRDs and should not be assumed reusable.\n```\n\n### 5. Consider Future CRD Compatibility\n\nFor types that may be used by multiple CRDs:\n\n**Option A: Keep in v1alpha1 package**\n- Simple, no import cycles\n- All types in one place\n- Risk: Package becomes too large\n\n**Option B: Extract to `pkg/apis/common`**\n- Clearer separation\n- Can be imported by multiple API groups\n- Risk: Import cycles with scheme registration\n\n**Recommendation:** Use Option A for now (keep all in `v1alpha1`). Revisit Option B when adding a second API group (e.g., `session.agentcube.volcano.sh`).\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files to Modify\n\n| File | Changes | Impact |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Add type usage documentation | Low - documentation only |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go` | Extract shared validation functions | Medium - affects validation tests |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Add comments marking shared types | Low - backward compatible |\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\nAll changes are **backward compatible**:\n- No existing type signatures change\n- Existing CRDs continue to work\n- Generated client-go code is unaffected\n\n### Testing Impact\n\n- Existing unit tests continue to pass\n- May add tests for shared validation functions\n- No integration test changes needed\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Separate Common Package\n\nCreate `pkg/apis/common/types.go` for shared types.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Clear separation of concerns\n- Can be imported by multiple API groups\n\n**Cons:**\n- Import cycles with scheme registration\n- Over-engineering for single API group\n- More complex code generation setup\n\n**Decision:** Defer until we have multiple API groups.\n\n### Alternative 2: Use Kubernetes Core Types\n\nReplace `ResourceQuota` with `corev1.ResourceRequirements`.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Standard Kubernetes types\n- Better integration with ecosystem tools\n\n**Cons:**\n- `corev1.ResourceRequirements` is more complex than needed\n- Loses semantic clarity (our `ResourceQuota` has specific meaning)\n- Breaking change for existing CRDs\n\n**Decision:** Keep custom `ResourceQuota` but document mapping to core types.\n\n### Alternative 3: Generate Types from Schema\n\nUse kube-builder markers to generate types from a schema definition.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Single source of truth\n- Automatic validation generation\n\n**Cons:**\n- Significant refactoring effort\n- Loss of Go type safety during development\n- Complex toolchain setup\n\n**Decision:** Not justified for current project size.\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Add package-level documentation in `doc.go`\n- [ ] Add comments to shared types in `types.go`\n- [ ] Extract shared validation functions in `validation.go`\n- [ ] Update validation tests for extracted functions\n- [ ] Document patterns in `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **Multiple API Groups**: When adding `session.agentcube.volcano.sh`, reconsider shared type location\n2. **Webhook Validation**: Move validation to admission webhooks for better error messages\n3. **Defaulting Webhooks**: Consider separate defaulting functions for shared types\n4. **Conversion Webhooks**: Plan for v1alpha1 → v1beta1 migration path\n\n## References\n\n- [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n- [Kube-builder Book](https://book.kubebuilder.io/)\n- Deployment spec: `deployment/spec.md`\n- Client-go documentation: `deployment/client-go.md`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":31,"character":1},"end":{"line":31,"character":19}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"var \"localSchemeBuilder\" is unused","tags":[1]}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/register.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840319842,"end":1775840319852}}}}
